text: Palmer's tree frog (Hyloscirtus palmeri) is a frog. It lives in forests. In Costa Rica and Panama, it lives 200 to 900 meters above sea level. In Colombia's Cordillera Central (middle mountains), it lives 1600 meters above sea level. In the Chocoan Region in Colombia and Ecuador, it lives 100 to 1000 meters above sea level. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Palmer's tree frog
